                  <scopecontent id="aspace_e5d6c80f727a4a227a206911a69eeccf">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>Carbon typescript of a translation into French by David Gascoyne of an essay by Barker; signed by Barker and Gascoyne, with a brief explanatory typescript note by Barker. The original essay was titled "Therefore All Poems are Elegies."</p>
                     <p>Accompanied by pages 9-12 only of a typescript radio talk (in French) possibly broadcast in the BBC Overseas Service, discussing Barker's "The View from a Blind I." Approximately 1-1/2 pages are devoted to a critical assessment of the book, the remainder to a French translation of the poem "I Walked by a Window in Ireland," followed by the original English text. At the foot of page 12 is a pencilled note by Barker to "David" asking for a translation.</p>
                  </scopecontent>
               </c>
